# pyenv
#   For a library or binary, you may wish to ignore these over commit them
#   but for an app that you developer or run, it is better to have it
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if having platform-specific dependencies or dependencies
#   having no cross-platform support, pipenv may install dependencies that don't work, or even
#   fail to install. In that case, one can opt out of committing Pipfile.lock.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipenv, it is generally recommended to include poetry.lock in version control.
#   poetry.lock
#   # pyproject.toml is usually tracked.

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipenv, it is generally recommended to include pdm.lock in version control.
# .pdm.toml
# .pdm-python
# .pdm-build/

# PEP 582; used by e.g. github.com/fannheyward/coc-pyright
__pypackages__/

